acing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK12"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;padding:0px 8px 7px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div style="color: #001a81;"><a style="color: rgb(0, 26, 129); text-decoration: underline; " shape="rect" href="mailto:kathy.wells@firstpresby.net" linktype="2" target="_blank">Kathy Wells,</a></div><div><a style="color: rgb(0, 26, 129); text-decoration: underline; " shape="rect" href="mailto:kathy.wells@firstpresby.net" linktype="2" target="_blank">Financial Secretary</a><br /></div></td></tr></table><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK13"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;padding:0px 8px 7px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div style="color: #001a81;"><a style="color: rgb(0, 26, 129); text-decoration: underline;" href="mailto:russell.stewart@firstpresby.net" shape="rect" linktype="2" target="_blank">Russell Stewart,</a></div><div><a style="color: rgb(0, 26, 129); text-decoration: underline;" href="mailto:russell.stewart@firstpresby.net" shape="rect" linktype="2" target="_blank">Building Manager</a><br /></div><br /></td></tr></table><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr> <td style="padding-bottom:11px;height:1px;line-height:1px;" height="1" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"><img height="1" vspace="0" border="0" hspace="0" width="5" style="display: block;" alt="" src="http://img.constantcontact.com/letters/images/1101116784221/S.gif" /></td> </tr> </table>     <a name="LETTER.BLOCK15"></a><table style="background-color:#D96D1A;" bgcolor="#D96D1A" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK15"><tr><td style="padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 12pt;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><b>Solo Violin Recital</b></div></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK62"></a><table style="display: table; background-color: #ffffff;" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK62"><tr><td style="padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"><div style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #001a81;" size="3" face="Times"><div><span><strong>First Presbyterian Church</strong></span></div><div><span><strong>May 2, 7:30 p.m.</strong></span></div><table class="imgCaptionTable" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px;" width="185" align="center"><tr><td class="imgCaptionImg" style="text-align: center; color: #001a81;" width="185" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><a class="imgCaptionAnchor" track="on" shape="rect" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pp51KnZAZ1FS-CeNOdMkafUrERL9LcRWjSGahroTF0J9iHQElQnTV13BZBGOk8Io6H1F6vESrexWHNyWZHE1taLuM_TvmDz0xeRxPXb2ro0SIQRoRu7YBptkqz86s1V8AliuEg0O6MMheOONogoXFuXFtHtew2DRkRFUOhT57VGlLHV-jhV_oyelpYqqNvkLg2SCtuyvXdY=&c=&ch=" target="_blank"><img vspace="5" border="0" hspace="5" width="175" alt="Barber Violin Concerto mvt. 1 - Juliana Sharp" src="https://thumbnail.constantcontact.com/remoting/v1/vthumb/YOUTUBE/e79fddf6599a425394e85a31b619cfa8" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="imgCaptionText" style="text-align: center; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; color: rgb(0, 26, 129); font-size: 9pt;" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><div style="text-align: right;" align="right"><em>Juliana Sharp</em></div></td></tr></table></span></div></div><div style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; text-align: left;" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">You are cordially invited to the solo violin recital of Juliana Sharp, featuring works of Bruch and Saint-Saens, May 2, 7:30 p.m., First Presbyterian Church of Fairfield.</span></div><div style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&nbsp;</p><div style="text-align: left;" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><a style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-decoration: none;" track="on" shape="rect" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001pp51KnZAZ1FS-CeNOdMkafUrERL9LcRWjSGahroTF0J9iHQElQnTV13BZBGOk8IoCxHjpLuxsQl3gQJrvwBkqI_foTFLFsQmScnvi7J7Rhkn1tMTgCETqVjI6EUVmOGcKnL53p2kza6fzgWnuNxi4LLvpjqsiJVwP7_oedDq_Ds=&c=&ch=" linktype="1" target="_blank">Juliana Sharp</a>, a junior at Bunnell High School in Stratford began her violin studies at age 9. She is currently a student in Juilliard's Pre-College program. Among many accomplishments, she was a violinist in the Greater Bridgeport Youth Orchestras (GBYO) for six years, serving as the Assistant Concertmaster of the Principal Orchestra. Juliana has traveled and performed with the GBYO throughout Germany and Austria.</span></div><div style="text-align: left;" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></div><div style="text-align: left;" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>This event is free and open to the public. Refreshments will be served following the recital. Donations will benefit the Church's Music Fund.</span>&nbsp;</span></div></div></td></tr></table><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr> <td style="padding-bottom:11px;height:1px;line-height:1px;" height="1" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"><img height="1" vspace="0" border="0" hspace="0" width="5" style="display: block;" alt="" src="http://img.constantcontact.com/letters/images/1101116784221/S.gif" /></td> </tr> </table><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr> <td style="padding-bottom:11px;height:1px;line-height:1px;" height="1" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"><img height="1" vspace="0" border="0" hspace="0" width="5" style="display: block;" alt="" src="http://img.constantcontact.com/letters/images/1101116784221/S.gif" /></td> </tr> </table><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr> <td style="padding-bottom:11px;height:1px;line-height:1px;" height="1" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"><img height="1" vspace="0" border="0" hspace="0" width="5" style="display: block;" alt="" src="http://img.constantcontact.com/letters/images/1101116784221/S.gif" /></td> </tr> </table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK66"></a><table style="background-color:#D96D1A;" bgcolor="#D96D1A" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK66"><tr><td style="padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 12pt;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><b>Mission Trip Ghana</b></div><div><b><a style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-decoration: none;" shape="rect" href="mailto:hsmith4387@aol.com" linktype="2" target="_blank">Be a sponsor today!</a></b></div></td></tr></table><table style="background-color: #ffffff;" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK65"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;padding:0px 8px 0px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"><div><img style="display: block;" height="143" vspace="0" border="0" name="ACCOUNT.IMAGE.183" hspace="0" width="196" src="http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs145/1103522065138/img/183.jpg" align="left" /></div><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><br /></td></tr></table></td> </tr> </table> <table style="width:190px;" border="0" width="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr> <td style="height:1px;line-height:1px;" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"><img height="1" vspace="0" border="0" hspace="0" width="5" style="display: block;" alt="" src="http://img.constantcontact.com/letters/images/1101116784221/S.gif" /></td> </tr> </table> </td> <td style="background:transparent;" valign="top" width="100%" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"> <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr> <td style="padding:0px 12px 0px 12px;" valign="top" width="100%" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center">    <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK19"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Georgia,Times New Roman,Times,Serif;font-size:10pt;padding:7px 8px 0px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="right"><div>April, 2014&nbsp;<br /></div></td></tr></table>  <a name="LETTER.BLOCK49"></a><table style="background-color:#8C2000;display: table; " bgcolor="#8C2000" border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK49"><tr><td style="color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;padding:5px 8px 5px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div style="text-align: -webkit-left;"><span style="color: #ffffff; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;" color="#ffffff" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>A Note from the Pastor</b></span></div></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK21"></a><table class="" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK21"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Georgia,Times New Roman,Times,Serif;font-size:10pt;padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><img style="display: block;" height="120" vspace="5" border="0" name="ACCOUNT.IMAGE.100" hspace="10" width="94" src="http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs145/1103522065138/img/100.jpg" align="right"><div><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><em>This mortal body must put on what is immortal&nbsp;(1 Corinthians 15:53).</em></p><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">Or so St. Paul said. &nbsp;</p><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">Here is a truth which clearly sustained the apostle through trials, tribulations, persecutions and problems. &nbsp;It was not only a truth, but also a saving story - the life, suffering, death and resurrection of Christ became a promise for St. Paul - that as a person trusts in Christ, Christ's victory over death fills his or her life, also.&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">First Presbyterian Church's Holy Week Schedule (Palm Sunday, Maundy Thursday, Good Friday and Easter Day) not only weaves day by day the salvation story, it becomes nothing less than a channel through which blessing and victory might flow into your story!&nbsp; Share the good news, pass this message along to a neighbor or friend.</p></div><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><div>Blessings!</div><div>Edward F. Duffy, Pastor<br />First Presbyterian Church of Fairfield</div></img></div></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK22"></a><table style="background-color:#8C2000;display: table; " bgcolor="#8C2000" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK22"><tr><td style="color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;padding:5px 8px 5px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><b>Holy Week Services and Events</b></div></td></tr></table>  <a name="LETTER.BLOCK23"></a><table style="display: table;" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK23"><tr><td style="padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); " valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><div style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">Attending an Easter service without first experiencing other Holy Week services is a little like watching the happy ending of a movie without seeing the events that made it so happy. First Presbyterian Church offers many ways to enter into the meaning and joy of Easter, so read on for details--and plan to attend!&nbsp;</span></div></div></td></tr></table>    <a name="LETTER.BLOCK56"></a><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK56"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Georgia,Times New Roman,Times,Serif;font-size:10pt;padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;" face="Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif"><img style="display: block;" src="http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs145/1103522065138/img/120.jpg" name="ACCOUNT.IMAGE.120" width="150" vspace="5" border="0" alt="Palm Sunday 3" align="right" height="100" hspace="10" /></span><div style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"><div style="color: #001a81;"><strong>Palm Sunday</strong></div><div style="color: #001a81;"><strong>April 13,&nbsp;</strong><strong>10:00 a.m.</strong></div>Palm Sunday will feature the congregational singing of "The Palms" as we celebrate the anniversary of Christ's entry into Jerusalem with the distribution of palm fronds and a procession by the children of the church.</span></div></div></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK57"></a><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK57"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Georgia,Times New Roman,Times,Serif;font-size:10pt;padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;" face="Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif"> <img style="display: block;" src="http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs145/1103522065138/img/117.jpg" name="ACCOUNT.IMAGE.117" width="150" vspace="5" border="0" alt="Maundy Thursday 2" align="right" height="99" hspace="10"> </img></span><div style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"><div style="color: #001a81;"><strong>Maundy Thursday</strong></div><div style="color: #001a81;"><strong>April 17,&nbsp;</strong><strong>7:30 p.m.</strong></div>Preceded by a Homemade Soup & Bread dinner (6:00 p.m.), Maundy Thursday is a Tenebrae service (Latin for "shadows"). &nbsp;In this service you will experience the darkness of Jesus' days before His resurrection; the betrayal, abandonment, and agony that He endured for us. This hauntingly beautiful service, which includes Communion, is left unfinished -because the story isn't over until Easter Day.</span></div></div></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK58"></a><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK58"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Georgia,Times New Roman,Times,Serif;font-size:10pt;padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;" face="Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif"> <img style="display: block;" src="http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs145/1103522065138/img/121.jpg" name="ACCOUNT.IMAGE.121" width="150" vspace="5" border="0" alt="Good Friday Breakfast" align="right" height="111" hspace="10"> </img></span><div style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"><div style="color: #001a81;"><strong>Good Friday Prayer Breakfast</strong></div><div style="color: #001a81;"><strong>April 18, 8</strong><strong>:30 a.m.</strong></div></span></div></div><div style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">Join us for an inspirational time of fellowship, food, music, and a&nbsp;<span>brief, beautiful worship service&nbsp;</span><em>Standing with Christ at the Cross.</em></div></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK59"></a><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK59"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Georgia,Times New Roman,Times,Serif;font-size:10pt;padding:7px 8px 7px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left"><div><div style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;text-align: center;" align="center"><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;"><div style="color: #001a81; text-align: left;" align="left"><strong>Easter Worship</strong></div><div style="color: #001a81; text-align: left;" align="left"><strong>April 20, 10</strong><strong>:00 a.m.</strong></div><div style="text-align: left;" align="left">First Presbyterian Church welcomes you to a triumphant celebration of the resurrection, featuring celebrated hymns from the congregation and Chancel Choir, bell choir, trumpet and tympani.</div></span></div></div></td></tr></table><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK63"><tr><td style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;padding:0px 8px 0px 8px;" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center"><div><img style="display: block;" name="ACCOUNT.IMAGE.123" border="0" width="335" src="http://ih.constantcontact.com/fs145/1103522065138/img/123.jpg" /></div></td></tr></table></td> </tr> </table> </td> </tr> </table> <table style="background:transparent;" border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr> <td style="padding:0px 12px 0px 12px;" valign="top" width="100%" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="center">       <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cell